ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v27.group

Class OMI_O23_ORDER

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractStructure
      • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractGroup
        • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v27.group.OMI_O23_ORDER
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Group, Structure, Visitable, Serializable

    public class OMI_O23_ORDER
extends AbstractGroup

    Represents a OMI_O23_ORDER group structure (a Group object). A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in/excluded together. This Group contains the following elements:

    • 1: ORC (Common Order)
    • 2: OMI_O23_TIMING (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 3: OBR (Observation Request)
    • 4: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating
    • 5: PRT (Participation Information) optional repeating
    • 6: CTD (Contact Data) optional
    • 7: DG1 (Diagnosis) optional repeating
    • 8: OMI_O23_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 9: IPC (Imaging Procedure Control Segment) repeating
    See Also:
